    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="631" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d631">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 18,
                                    1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Barnum telegraphs American property destroyed in Harpoot $100,000
                            probably. I have notified the Porte would expect prompt payment for <pb facs="0608" n="1342" xml:id="pg_1342"/> all damages when extent is
                            known. Telegram states that shell burst in missionary house; that
                            soldiers protected raiders and joined in plunder, and that multitudes
                            were killed in that province. Persons of missionaries there
                            protected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
